## 🎯 The Problem

> India's ~600 million agriculture-dependent population includes roughly **86% smallholder farmers** — yet despite improving forecast accuracy, no widely deployed tool actually translates a weather forecast into a specific, same-day farm decision.

Farmers either don't receive forecasts in a usable form, or receive raw meteorological data — *"60% chance of rain"* — that they aren't equipped to turn into an irrigate, spray, or harvest decision on their own. The interpretation gap, not the data itself, is where the value is lost.

<br>

## 💡 The Solution

Kisan Saathi answers the specific question a farmer actually asks — ***should I irrigate today, should I spray before the rain, should I delay harvest*** — as a plain **YES / NO / WAIT** verdict, personalized to the farmer's crop and its current growth stage, backed by a one-line reason they can verify against their own field.

<div align="center">

| Instead of... | Kisan Saathi shows... |
|:---|:---|
| "60% chance of rain, 12mm expected" | 🚫 **Skip irrigating today** — rain expected in 18 hrs |
| "Wind 14 km/h, humidity 78%" | ✅ **Spray now** — dry window before tomorrow's rain |
| Raw 7-day temperature grid | ⏳ **Wait 2 days to harvest** — grain moisture too high |

</div>

<br>

## 📱 Screens

<div align="center">

| # | Screen | Purpose |
|:-:|:---|:---|
| 1 | **Onboarding** | Crop, sowing date, farm setup |
| 2 | **Home** | Today's decision cards + active severe-weather alert |
| 3 | **Decision Detail** | Verdict, plain-language reasoning, feedback loop |
| 4 | **Severe Alert Detail** | Protective action for the current crop stage |
| 5 | **Alerts List** | Active + historical severe-weather warnings |
| 6 | **7-Day Forecast** | Icon-first day strip |
| 7 | **My Farm** | Crop, sowing date, stage, location, water source |
| 8 | **Track Record** | Season accuracy score, verdict history |

</div>

<br>

## 🎨 Design System

<div align="center">

<img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Sky-3E6D9C?style=for-the-badge" height="28"/> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Soil-6B4A2F?style=for-the-badge" height="28"/> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Go--Green-3B7A4A?style=for-the-badge" height="28"/> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Amber-B4691F?style=for-the-badge" height="28"/> <img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Alert--Red-B23A2E?style=for-the-badge" height="28"/>

</div>

| Token | Value | Usage |
|:---|:---|:---|
| Sky | `#3E6D9C` | Weather elements, primary chrome |
| Soil | `#6B4A2F` | Crop and field-related content |
| Go-Green | `#3B7A4A` | "Do it today" verdicts |
| Amber | `#B4691F` | "Wait" verdicts |
| Alert Red | `#B23A2E` | Severe-weather banners *only* — reserved, never decorative |

**Typography** — `Fraunces` for headlines · `Inter` for body/UI · `Space Mono` for numbers and data

**Core principle** — the farmer should never have to interpret a raw probability. Every screen leads with a plain verdict icon; forecast detail is available only on request.

<br>

