## 🚀 Try It

No build step, no dependencies — just open it in a browser.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/kisan-saathi.git
cd kisan-saathi
open KisanSaathi_Prototype.html
```

Tap through the bottom tab bar and decision cards to walk the full flow: **Home → Decision Detail → Alerts → Forecast → My Farm → Track Record.**

<br>

## 🔄 Design Process

<div align="center">

**Discover** → **Define** → **Ideate** → **Design** → **Prototype & Test**

</div>

Built following a full 5-phase Human-Centered Design process. Every phase — background research, user personas, empathy maps, journey maps, HMW statements, Crazy 8 / SCAMPER ideation, information architecture, and a usability test plan — is documented in the case study `.docx`.

<br>

## 🔍 Research Highlights

- 🌏 **86%** of India's farmers are smallholders, out of a **600M**-strong agriculture-dependent population
- 📈 A Telangana field study found **90%** of farmers who received usable forecasts said it improved their planting decisions
- 🔇 Existing advisory systems (SMS, government portals) are largely **one-way** — no way for a farmer to flag a wrong call, which erodes trust fast
- 🌾 Roughly **half** of India's cultivated area is rain-fed with no canal or borewell fallback — a missed forecast window can mean a full reseeding

